♪ And, Kayleigh, could we get it
together again... ♪

02:05.880 --> 02:07.760
What the fuck are you doing?

02:07.760 --> 02:08.920
Nothing.

02:08.920 --> 02:11.280
My mum just wanted me to...

02:11.280 --> 02:13.520
...try her fur coat on for size.

02:13.520 --> 02:14.880
It's nothing.

02:14.880 --> 02:17.280
How did you know
I was in here anyway?

02:17.280 --> 02:19.080
Where else would you be?

02:19.080 --> 02:22.320
Everyone knows this is all
you've got left, Dimlo.

02:22.320 --> 02:24.760
Well, it's a good thing
you're here, Barney.

02:24.760 --> 02:27.560
Opportunity knocks.
I'm off to Alabasas.

02:29.120 --> 02:31.520
Pay me what you owe
and then you can fuck off.

02:31.520 --> 02:33.360
No, no, no, you don't understand.

02:33.360 --> 02:36.240
I'm here to offer you Peckham boys
a deal of a lifetime.

02:36.240 --> 02:37.720
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

02:37.720 --> 02:40.240
90 Atari consoles.

02:40.240 --> 02:42.800
30 Amstrad 790s.

02:42.800 --> 02:45.120
50 soda streams.
And I mean the good ones.

02:45.120 --> 02:47.520
Got Dorothy Perkins fur coats.

02:47.520 --> 02:50.080
Fila BJs - not the snides.

02:50.080 --> 02:52.240
Casio calculator watches.

02:52.240 --> 02:55.720
300 copies of Dark Side Of The Moon.
Yeah, I've got it. Come on, then.

02:55.720 --> 02:57.520
What's the catch?

02:59.400 --> 03:00.840
There ain't one.

03:01.880 --> 03:04.160
- How much?
- Five grand.

03:04.160 --> 03:06.000
No.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.240
Two grand.

03:07.240 --> 03:10.360
Well, that was easier than
pushing a granny over in the snow.

03:10.360 --> 03:12.880
Come to my office
and collect the readies.

03:12.880 --> 03:14.400
I'm not coming back here.

03:14.400 --> 03:16.080
State of it.

03:17.120 --> 03:18.400
Full of rats.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.480
And fucking Lords.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.120
What the fuck do you want?

03:58.760 --> 04:00.000
Grandma sent me.

04:08.400 --> 04:10.320
You wanted a silencer, right?

04:12.800 --> 04:14.040
Yeah.

04:15.200 --> 04:17.400
You wanna know where
those bullets are headed?

04:17.400 --> 04:20.320
It's just a warning.
Yeah, it might get ugly, Kel.

04:23.080 --> 04:24.800
His name's Eddie Smith.

04:24.800 --> 04:28.240
Cindy's fella. He's just got out of
the nick and he's game.

04:28.240 --> 04:31.240
What do you mean, he's game?
I heard he ironed someone out.

04:36.320 --> 04:38.600
You know what you do
- with that, yeah?
- Yeah.

04:39.640 --> 04:41.120
It's not my first rodeo.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.360
You've never even ridden
a fuckin' horse.

04:54.240 --> 04:56.080
♪ When two tribes go to war

04:56.080 --> 04:59.720
♪ A point is all that you can score

04:59.720 --> 05:01.800
♪ Score them all, score them all

05:01.800 --> 05:03.640
♪ When two tribes go to war

05:03.640 --> 05:07.040
♪ A point is all that you can score

05:07.040 --> 05:09.360
♪ Working for the black gas

05:09.360 --> 05:12.920
♪ Yeah! ♪

05:15.320 --> 05:16.680
Let me guess.

05:16.680 --> 05:18.360
White, one sugar?

05:23.080 --> 05:24.320
Adelante.

05:29.560 --> 05:33.680
Firstly... let me apologise
for the grand entrance

05:33.680 --> 05:36.040
and the flashing lights
at Club Paradiso.

05:36.040 --> 05:38.200
It really wasn't necessary.

05:38.200 --> 05:41.560
But we've never had a chance
to show off like that.

05:41.560 --> 05:43.920
You see, until you arrived,

05:43.920 --> 05:47.720
the only deaths in this part
of the Costa were the elderly.

05:47.720 --> 05:51.200
And now, well, I'm at a loss,
you know.

05:51.200 --> 05:52.920
I was hoping you could fill me in.

05:54.360 --> 05:56.160
You're the policeman.

05:56.160 --> 05:58.320
Well, it's, um...

05:58.320 --> 06:01.080
...it's clear that
your uncle was out of his depth.

06:02.360 --> 06:05.480
Now, witnesses place
you and Cindy Carter

06:05.480 --> 06:06.920
having lunch with him

06:06.920 --> 06:10.400
the day he rowed with
Ernesto Alvarez at Club Paradiso.

06:10.400 --> 06:12.640
But, from my memory,
you saw nothing.

06:16.360 --> 06:20.720
Furious, Tony went to Escobells
with a gun and confronted Ernesto.

06:21.760 --> 06:23.720
All hell broke loose.

06:23.720 --> 06:25.720
Everybody presumed dead...

06:26.800 --> 06:31.160
Until Ernesto was found alive
with a bullet in his chest.

06:31.160 --> 06:35.200
And I told Cindy that he was
recovering in hospital.

06:38.080 --> 06:40.400
Sadly, he succumbed to his injuries.

06:42.600 --> 06:44.400
But just before he died...

06:44.400 --> 06:46.080
...he had a visitor.

06:54.520 --> 06:56.240
And they left...

06:56.240 --> 06:58.840
...this earring behind.

07:16.840 --> 07:18.600
Don't cry, darling.

07:20.360 --> 07:22.840
We don't shoot our wounded
in this family.

07:24.240 --> 07:26.280
When Gene made a pledge to you...

07:26.280 --> 07:28.360
...we all did.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.720
Thanks, Ma.

07:32.240 --> 07:35.600
So why on earth do they think
Gene killed someone?

07:38.480 --> 07:40.480
The guy that murdered Tony...

07:40.480 --> 07:42.280
...Ernesto Alvarez,

07:42.280 --> 07:43.880
he died in hospital.

07:45.000 --> 07:46.520
They think Gene did it.

07:49.120 --> 07:51.480
No-good cunts. All of 'em.

07:52.560 --> 07:56.160
Just cos they eat octopus don't make
the police down here any better.

07:57.920 --> 08:00.120
My boy, a killer?

08:01.720 --> 08:03.240
Are they mad?

08:19.400 --> 08:21.080
Now, you know what I think?

08:29.240 --> 08:33.040
I think that, while you
paid respects to your uncle,

08:33.040 --> 08:35.520
Cindy took revenge for his murder

08:35.520 --> 08:38.400
and left this little souvenir behind.

08:41.480 --> 08:45.000
Tell me I'm right and you can
walk out of here a free man.

08:47.400 --> 08:48.920
Do you know what I think?

08:48.920 --> 08:51.720
Go, please, tell me, amigo.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.040
I think that if you had anything
that resembled real evidence,

08:56.040 --> 08:57.840
you'd have arrested her, and not me.

08:59.920 --> 09:01.960
As it is, you're just
shaking the tree

09:01.960 --> 09:03.880
to see if anything falls, I get it.

09:06.560 --> 09:08.720
You're sensing
I might be the weak link.

09:11.200 --> 09:14.120
The truth is, you've got nothing
and you know it.

09:16.880 --> 09:18.160
Look at you.

09:19.200 --> 09:20.640
A sheriff...

09:21.960 --> 09:24.760
...of a sleepy one-horse town
with zero crime,

09:24.760 --> 09:26.160
and then boom...

09:27.240 --> 09:29.520
...it all kicks off
when the Lords ride in.

09:30.880 --> 09:34.320
Like something out of a two-bob
airport novella, ain't it?

09:37.080 --> 09:39.640
Most of the English over here
are criminals.

09:41.120 --> 09:42.680
But not all of us.

09:47.280 --> 09:49.360
So unless you're gonna charge me...

09:50.960 --> 09:52.320
...time to salir.

10:00.480 --> 10:02.040
Tea's shit, mate.

10:36.840 --> 10:38.040
So...

10:38.040 --> 10:42.120
...looks like the apple didn't fall
so far from the tree after all.

10:43.200 --> 10:44.840
Look, I'm sorry, Dad.

10:47.400 --> 10:50.160
The man who killed Uncle Tony
died in the hospital.

10:50.160 --> 10:52.040
They was just asking me about him.

10:52.040 --> 10:53.560
What did you say?

10:53.560 --> 10:55.760
Nothing. I don't know anything.

10:55.760 --> 10:57.640
Then what you sorry about, hm?

11:01.120 --> 11:03.440
I didn't mean to embarrass you.

11:06.320 --> 11:08.200
You avoiding me is embarrassing.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.000
Not coming home for Christmas...

11:10.000 --> 11:11.240
...embarrassing.

11:12.440 --> 11:14.000
But getting arrested...

11:16.680 --> 11:18.000
You drive.

11:29.080 --> 11:30.280
A-hem.

11:31.520 --> 11:35.400
- What?
- Your partner's widow,
Mrs Russo is here.

11:35.400 --> 11:37.000
- Now?
- Yeah.

11:37.000 --> 11:39.520
For fuck's sake.
All right, bring her in.

11:48.560 --> 11:49.760
Hiya.

11:50.920 --> 11:52.600
Thanks for coming down.

11:52.600 --> 11:54.160
Do you mind?

11:54.160 --> 11:56.440
No, of course not.

11:57.560 --> 12:00.600
Been on my own with him
since his dad was murdered.

12:02.600 --> 12:04.080
There we go.

12:06.480 --> 12:08.200
Do you wanna take a seat?

12:15.680 --> 12:17.120
I, er...

12:18.360 --> 12:19.880
...I just wanted to reassure you

12:19.880 --> 12:22.680
we're doing everything we can
to find David's killers.

12:24.760 --> 12:27.680
You know, my husband thought
you were the bee's knees.

12:27.680 --> 12:30.640
The way you brought him up
- from traffic duty.
- Yeah.

12:30.640 --> 12:32.520
He rated you.

12:33.640 --> 12:35.080
He was a good lad.

12:38.320 --> 12:41.200
They're gonna pay
for what they took from you.

12:41.200 --> 12:43.520
You have my word on it.

12:43.520 --> 12:45.640
I heard they fled the country.

12:46.800 --> 12:47.840
Yeah.

12:47.840 --> 12:50.440
Unfortunately, yeah.

12:50.440 --> 12:52.320
And you let 'em escape.

12:53.720 --> 12:56.000
We're gonna find them, Amelia.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.240
I promise you, whatever it takes.

12:59.240 --> 13:00.840
Fighting talk.

13:00.840 --> 13:02.240
I like it.

13:04.400 --> 13:06.400
But my David is dead.

13:08.000 --> 13:11.120
And whatever comfort I may have had
in seeing justice done...

13:13.600 --> 13:15.000
...that's gone too.

13:16.120 --> 13:19.560
And it's your fucking fault... woman.

13:31.800 --> 13:33.840
'What did the police do to you?'

13:33.840 --> 13:35.240
Just digging.

13:35.240 --> 13:37.720
- They found your earrings.
- Fuck!

13:37.720 --> 13:40.520
Without the other one,
they can't prove it's yours.

13:40.520 --> 13:42.320
They've got nothing.

13:42.320 --> 13:43.760
Right?

13:43.760 --> 13:46.520
They can't pin anything on us,
we're in the clear.

13:46.520 --> 13:48.040
I promise.

13:48.040 --> 13:49.680
We're home free.

13:49.680 --> 13:51.800
No, we're not.

13:52.920 --> 13:55.840
Your brother's worked out
the land's worth 50 grand.

13:55.840 --> 13:58.120
He said he'd tell your dad
they should flip it

13:58.120 --> 13:59.840
and fuck off back to Bermondsey.

14:01.800 --> 14:03.400
Well, that's not happening.

14:03.400 --> 14:05.920
Cind, we ain't come this far
for nothing.

14:08.960 --> 14:11.440
Maybe you should tell him
about the hotel.

14:11.440 --> 14:14.720
You know, try and get him
- on the hook.
- Have you met my dad?

14:14.720 --> 14:17.760
He'd never entertain the idea
of us building on that land,

14:17.760 --> 14:19.800
because he didn't think of it himself.

14:20.840 --> 14:22.480
That's his mentality.

14:24.480 --> 14:27.640
That's why I got as far away
from him as I possibly could.

14:30.120 --> 14:32.440
Well, whether you like it or not,

14:32.440 --> 14:35.200
he owns the land now,
and we need him.

14:35.200 --> 14:38.480
Cos if they sell up and go back
to London, we're stuck here.

14:38.480 --> 14:41.480
Potless. Squatting in
someone else's house.

14:41.480 --> 14:43.560
Like Uncle fucking Tony.

14:44.920 --> 14:47.800
What's the weather like out there?
'Sunshine and blue skies.'

14:47.800 --> 14:51.720
Kids flying kites.'Typical. Sun
only comes out when you go away.'

14:51.720 --> 14:53.640
Where you at with that lock-up?

14:53.640 --> 14:56.600
'It's sorted, Dad.'Good boy.
How much d'you get?

14:57.640 --> 15:00.000
What?'You heard.'

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
Yeah, pushed him hard, Dad.

15:02.000 --> 15:05.280
He went over like a granny
in the snow.'How much?'

15:05.280 --> 15:07.840
'A few grand.'Good.
Well, get that money sharpish.

15:07.840 --> 15:10.640
We ain't got money to eat
and God knows how long it'll take

15:10.640 --> 15:12.600
to sell that land.
'Yeah, sweet, Dad.'

15:12.600 --> 15:15.680
So, what's it like there, anyway?
Nice birds?

15:15.680 --> 15:16.960
Listen, Kel.

15:16.960 --> 15:19.160
You're the only one I trust.

15:19.160 --> 15:21.960
And I need my general,
here with me. You get it?

15:21.960 --> 15:24.880
Yeah, that's cushty, Dad.
Really cushty.

15:24.880 --> 15:28.000
Hey, we'll have a nice bit of
lobster when I get out there.

15:28.000 --> 15:29.800
'Lobster? I fucking hate lobster.

15:29.800 --> 15:31.800
'You know how much
that land is worth?'

15:31.800 --> 15:34.720
£50,000 for the Lords.

15:36.400 --> 15:38.280
'Fucking hell.'Yeah, exactly.

15:38.280 --> 15:40.560
That's plenty for us
to get back in the game.

15:40.560 --> 15:43.440
We'll be back in south London
and on top before you know it.

15:43.440 --> 15:45.120
Ow! God, it stings!

15:45.120 --> 15:47.480
You should've used the Piz Buin
I gave you.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.880
- Len, ssh!
- Sorry, Dad.

15:50.960 --> 15:52.680
Kel, it's Ma.

15:52.680 --> 15:54.000
'All right, Mum?'

15:54.000 --> 15:58.200
That little thing,
I asked you to do. Any good?

15:58.200 --> 16:00.480
Yeah. Yeah.

16:00.480 --> 16:02.840
Name's Eddie Smith.
He's a right wrong 'un.

16:02.840 --> 16:06.480
He lives up on the flats
on Nelson Wa... Way.

16:06.480 --> 16:09.960
'Good boy. You gonna flop on him?'

16:09.960 --> 16:12.520
Oh! Fucking wanker!

16:12.520 --> 16:15.040
Your kid brother deserves
to know the truth.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.400
Don't you think?

16:16.400 --> 16:20.120
'It's all in hand, Ma. I got the
yogga. I'm gonna stick it on him.'

16:20.120 --> 16:21.360
That's it.

16:21.360 --> 16:24.520
All I ask is that
we look out for each other.

16:29.200 --> 16:30.760
Piss off.

16:52.680 --> 16:54.000
No.

16:54.000 --> 16:57.480
I will not sit here
and listen to you masticating.

16:57.480 --> 17:01.640
Then licking the crisp dust off your
fingertips. It's disgusting, no.

17:07.760 --> 17:09.600
What do you think he's up to?

17:09.600 --> 17:11.240
I don't know.

17:11.240 --> 17:13.160
We just need something illegal.

17:13.160 --> 17:16.760
Stolen goods, theft,
anything with a bit of jail time.

17:16.760 --> 17:19.520
That way we can get him
to roll over on the brother

17:19.520 --> 17:21.360
before he fucks off to Spain.

17:21.360 --> 17:23.560
Without Kelly, we can't get to Gene.

17:23.560 --> 17:25.320
Without Gene, we're fucked.

17:52.320 --> 17:53.600
Hello?

18:09.480 --> 18:12.680
What the fuck are you doing here?
Don't shoot, don't shoot!

18:12.680 --> 18:15.960
- Are you trying to rob me?
- No,
I'm not, I'm a friend of Cindy's.

18:15.960 --> 18:17.720
- Cindy's?
- Yeah.

18:17.720 --> 18:19.080
Cindy.

18:19.080 --> 18:20.720
How do you know my mother?

18:21.920 --> 18:23.240
Mother?

